            <title>[CAMEL-20380] Kafka Batch Consumer: doesn&apos;t honor the poll timeout set</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-20380</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As far as I see from some tests done on Camel-Kamelets, the poll timeout is not honored while batching. At least from my experiments, if you set a batch of 10 messages and poll timeout of 5000 ms, if you send one single message, it will be immediately sent to next step in the route, without waiting for poll timeout to end.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
